  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Mobile Application (Android) Developer",
  "description": "<h2>Company Overview</h2><p>Far Stream Technologies was Incorporated in April 2020 by a team of business owner that are passionate on addressing the market needs for a more efficient, robust, and service orientated solution for mobile device security and management.</p><h2>Job Summary</h2><p>The Mobile Application (Android) Developer role is to provide developing and technical support to our enterprise customers. The ideal candidate will be deployed onsite and will be on a 5-day work week schedule. He/She will also be required to perform all app testing and fixing of bugs discovered during the development phase.<br /></p><h3>Responsibilities</h3><ul><li>Develop and test Android mobile applications/programme to meet enterprise customer requirements and enhance mobile device security and management solutions.</li><li>Deliver technical support onsite to enterprise customers, resolving issues to ensure seamless application performance.</li><li>Conduct comprehensive testing of Android applications to identify and document bugs during the development phase.</li><li>Diagnose and resolve application bugs efficiently to improve app stability and user experience.</li><li>Collaborate with customer cross-functional teams to implement fixes and enhancements based on testing outcomes and customer feedback.</li></ul><h3>Desired Skills & Experience:</h3><ul><li>Experience with on-site deployment, debugging and customer support.</li><li>Communicate fluently in English - spoken and written.</li><li>Resourcefulness, ability to problem-solve in a systematic approach.</li><li>Good organization skill and able to work independently.</li><li>Possess the right attitude to learn and execute with sense of urgency.</li></ul><h3>Technical Competency</h3><p>Currently, we are looking for a contract position to complete the following outstanding work:</p><p>1) Develop script for Linux OS hardening.<br />2) Develop script to conduct System Testing.<br />3) Develop Android programme based on Open SSL library for Bluetooth encryption and verification.  </p><h3>Education:</h3><p>ITE / Diploma in Engineering or Information Technology preferred but not essential.</p><p>Fresh graduate are welcome to apply.<br /><br />Other Technical Certification (eg: C++, Kotlin, Linux, etc) will be advantages.</p><h3></h3><p>*We regret that only shortlisted candidates will be notified.</p>",
